  "text": "The assumption of balanced budget implies that the policy space is unidimensional, since each level of T corresponds to a unique tax rate and vice-versa. Given that leisure is a normal good we have that there is a unique equilibrium in which the individual choice of leisure, the tax rate and the lump-sum redistribution are uniquely determined. Following [CITATION_1] , we know that if redistributive preferences of voters are monotonically related to their wage rate (which is the case given that pre-tax income is monotonically increasing with productivity), then a Condorcet winner exists and coincides with the preferred tax rate of the voter with median wage rate.",
